column3: "Altogether 91 active air samples were obtained between Dec 3 2006 and Feb 24 2007 from the seven major cities of India: New Delhi and Agra in the north, Kolkata in the east, Mumbai and Goa in the west and Bangalore and Chennai in the south."
column7: number of observations per site is unclear; assumed that observations were distributed approximately evenly across sites; "Precisely, short-term high resolution samples of 12 h duration (day, 8:00 a.m.-8:00 p.m.; night, 8:00 p.m.-8:00 a.m.) were collected. Altogether 91 active air samples were obtained between Dec 3 2006 and Feb 24 2007 from the seven major cities of India: New Delhi and Agra in the north, Kolkata in the east, Mumbai and Goa in the west and Bangalore and Chennai in the south. Sampling sites are shown in Fig. 1."
column18: "Detection limits were derived from the blanks and quantified as the mean plus three times the standard deviation of the concentration in the blanks, based on 12 h sampling. The limit of detection (LOD) for every PCB congener was determined by adding three standard deviations (average ± 3 x SD) to the average of the blanks. Values smaller than the LOD were not included in the calculation. Each PCB congener in the samples was blank corrected. LOD values varied from 0.05 to 0.42 ng/sample for PUF samples and from 0.00023 to 0.00146 ng/sample and for QFF with the highest LODs observed for trichlorinated congeners."

Values smaller than the LOD were not included in the calculation. Each PCB congener in the samples was blank corrected. LOD values varied from 0.05 to 0.42 ng/sample for PUF samples and from 0.00023 to 0.00146 ng/sample and for QFF with the highest LODs observed for trichlorinated congeners."

column3: "The sampling area was the West African region as shown in Figure 1 including sites in parts of the West African continent (The Gambia, Sierra Leone, Ivory Coast, and Ghana), parts of the ocean ca. 400 km off the West African coast, and on the island of Sao Vicente in Cape Verde island (16° 51' N; 24° 58' W) situated ca. 1000 km off the West African coast."
column6: cruise from Germany to South Africa
column7: "Twelve-hour high-volume air samples were collected on board the RV Polarstern between 25 and 0.65° N on 5-10 November 2007 during a cruise from Germany to South Africa. Air samples were taken on the observation deck, about 20 m above sea level. Four high-volume air samplers were placed at four corners of the ship, two on the observation deck (starboard and port) and two on the back deck of the ship (starboard and port). More details about the sampling procedure are given in the Supporting Information (SI; section S.1)."
column18: "Samples were blank corrected using the mean of the field blanks, and the method detection limits (MDL) were derived from the field blanks and quantified as 3 times the standard deviation of the blank concentrations."

column7: "Passive samplers (polyurethane foam (PUF) disks) were deployed in four West African countries - Ghana, Ivory Coast, Sierra Leone, and The Gambia...Six passive samplers and a field blank were deployed and collected in each country, but results from only 5 passive samplers are reported for Ivory Coast and Ghana, 4 from the Gambia, and 1 from Sierra Leone because the rest of the samples could not be quantified due to sample interferences...The length of the exposure time averaged about 90 days from May to July 2008."
